    "LTL",
    "ltl"
  ],
  "school": "ICT",
  "definition": "A swing high or low that forms from a reaction off a higher time frame PD array or point of interest, validated when a short-term high/low appears on the opposite side.",
  "identification_rules": [
    "Locate a higher time frame PD array or point of interest where price reacts.",
    "Observe the formation of a short-term swing high/low at that reaction.",
    "Confirm when a short-term high/low forms on the opposite side of the initial reactive swing.",
    "Once the opposite short-term high/low appears, the swing becomes a validated long-term high/low."
  ],
  "trading_implication": "Long-term highs and lows represent the most significant structural levels on the current time frame. They act as key reference points for bias, often not expected to be violated, and can be used as targets or reversal zones.",
  "common_mistakes": [
    "Prematurely labeling a swing as long-term before a short-term high/low forms on the other side."
  ],
